{
  "\u0026nbsp;\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=home\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4983\u0026\"\u003e\u003cIMG BORDER=0 ALIGN=absmiddle HSPACE=2 SRC=\"http://images.commissioner.com/images/wizard/win95/x.gif\"\u003e\u003c/A\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003c/TABLE\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003cTR\u003e",
  ", QB DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/14/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBatch had a huge game against Minnesota, throwing for 345 yards and three scores. He's still not worth starting on a weekly basis despite the performance, but he might now warrant a reserve role in deeper leagues. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4983\u0026key=187388\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBubba Franks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE GB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/14/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFranks caught only two passes for four yards against the Ravens, but both catches resulted in TDs. Franks has clearly emerged as a primary goal-line threat on one of the NFL's top offensive units.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4983\u0026key=1790\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDavid Patten\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NE - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZ!",
  ", QB MIA - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/14/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFiedler threw for 213 yards and a score against the N.Y. Jets, but he was also picked off twice. He's still not a very reliable Fantasy player, and is no better than a reserve at this point. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4983\u0026key=1160\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eLamar Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB MIA - Neal/McKay \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/14/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith had a decent outing on Sunday, posting 77 yards of total offense and a touchdown against the N.Y. Jets. He did fumble twice in the game, but he's still good enough to be a No. 1 back from a Fantasy perspective. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4983\u0026key=187742\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eLaveranues Coles\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NYJ - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003e!",
  ", WR DEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/14/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eKennison caught six passes for 84 yards and a TD at Seattle. Don't expect Kennison to suddenly turn his career and season around with one solid outing. He might follow his good game with many weeks of statistical silence,\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4983\u0026key=187382\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eShaun Alexander\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB SEA - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/14/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAlexander had another great game, rushing for 142 yards and two TDs on 33 carries against Denver. Alexander has clearly established himself as a Fantasy standout, and he has ignited the Seattle offense. If he continues to play at his current level, he might hold onto the feature back job, even when Ricky Watters returns.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsl!",
  ", WR NE - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/14/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBrown had a great outing against San Diego, posting 11 catches for 117 yards against San Diego. With Terry Glenn returning, Brown could become a pretty relaible Fantasy player facing No. 2 cornerbacks on a weekly basis. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4983\u0026key=1212\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDarnay Scott\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CIN - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/14/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eScott caught only one pass for five yards against the Browns, but he scored on his only reception.   "Dixon missed Monday night's 10-9 loss to the Philadelphia Eagles due to a sprained ankle.   "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Big E '01 10/23/01",
  "Taylor has been ruled out of Sunday's game against Baltimore and his status for next week's game remains uncertain. \"All I know is that, from week to week, they increase his exercises and change of direction,\" head coach Tom Coughlin told \u003ci\u003eThe Florida Times-Union\u003c/i\u003e. \"It remains to be seen when Fred will be able to play. Progress is slow. I'm hoping he responds well this week, then we can make some kind of legitimate guess [about a return date] next week.\" Taylor has been inactive since severely injuring his groin on Sept 23.   \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=1886\u0026key=187617\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDennis Northcutt\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CLE - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eNorthcutt left Sunday's game because of a concussion.   "The Chicago Sun-Times\u003c/I\u003e is now reporting that Dez White will start in place of Robinson, with Terrell being used as the team's third receiver. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=1886\u0026key=1282\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Martin\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR ATL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMartin will have an X-ray on his broken right collarbone this week. The team feels confident that Martin will be available for their Nov. 11 game against Dallas, so Fantasy owners should keep him on reserve until then. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=1886\u0026key=1183\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRob Moore\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR ARI - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAccording to Cardinals coach Dave McGinnis, Moore may not play a regular season game !",
  "To": "martin.cuilla@enron.com",
  "Todd Heap\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE BAL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHeap did not play Sunday but head coach Brian Billick told \u003ci\u003eThe Baltimore Sun\u003c/i\u003e he is optimistic that the rookie will play in this week's game. Heap has been inactive for the last four games because of a sprained ankle. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=1886\u0026key=1177\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTerry Allen\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BAL - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAllen, who left after the fifth play of Sunday's game with a sprained ankle, is questionable for this week's game. Jason Brookins will start at running back if Allen is inactive. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=1886\u0026key=1035\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eElvis Grbac\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB BAL - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003e!",
  "Updated 10/22/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003ePanthers Head Coach George Seifert said Monday that Huntley will enter Week Seven as the team's starting tailback. \"He has progressed from the standpoint that he is now healthy,\" said Seifert. \"Here's a golden opportunity.\" See if Huntley is still available in your league, as he looks to be the first player given a shot to claim the Carolina starting RB job.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=1886\u0026key=12405\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJacquez Green\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR TB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/22/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGreen suffered a left hip sprain during Sunday's game against Pittsburgh.   "Bouman is now listed as probable for Sunday's game.   "Gannon has been a top-flight Fantasy QB this year.   "Garcia, whose practice time was limited all week, played in Saturday's game. He admitted afterwards that he has a cracked rib.   "\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cIMG HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2 WIDTH=14 HEIGHT=14 SRC=\"http": "//images.commissioner.com/images/eye_device_tiny.gif\"\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e\u003cFONT COLOR=\"#ffffff\"\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMake Selection\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e",
  "A banged-up Smith hasn't done much statistically in recent weeks. He isn't very explosive, however, and won't help Fantasy teams much during Weeks 15 through 17.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2079\u0026key=235174\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Weinke\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB CAR - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Consider Weinke as a backup during the Fantasy playoffs. He lacks the weapons to post better-than-average numbers, but he is a good option if you need an emergency QB. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2079\u0026key=12797\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eKurt Warner\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB STL - Hunter \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWarner should guide many Fantasy teams to success during the playoffs. Expect fine numbers from him the rest of the way.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1034\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRich Gannon\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB OAK - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGannon has been a top-flight Fantasy QB this year. He will be a key player on many title teams, and should never be benched. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",

  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Graham probably won't play Sunday at Kansas City because of the death of his father in a car accident, coach Mike Riley said Friday. The Chargers are already missing their No. 3 receiver, Tim Dwight, due to complications of a collapsed lung. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2079\u0026key=1663\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAntowain Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB NE - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith rushed for a career-high 156 yards and a touchdown Saturday.   "Gramatica injured his hamstring in the fourth quarter on Sunday.   "Gannon has been a top-flight Fantasy QB this year.   "Garcia, whose practice time was limited all week, played in Saturday's game. He admitted afterwards that he has a cracked rib.   "Alexander (leg) was placed on injured reserve, officially ending his season. Walter Rasby will continue to start in his place, but Zeron Flemister has emerged as the team's best receiving tight end with Alexander out. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=12429\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMatt Hasselbeck\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SEA - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe \u003ci\u003eSeattle Times\u003c/i\u003e says Hasselbeck's season might be over. Mike Holmgren said he would only use him in an emergency this week, and the Seahawks coach may elect to have Hasselbeck use the season's final two games to rest his injured shoulder. Trent Dilfer will start at San Diego this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=133462\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAmos Zereoue\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Fri, 28 Dec 2001 03:15:16 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Gramatica sat out practice Wednesday, but is expected to test his injured leg on Thursday. Doug Brien and Brad Daluiso worked out Wednesday for the Buccaneers, who might sign one if Martin Gramatica can't kick against the Baltimore Ravens this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=12429\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMatt Hasselbeck\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SEA - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTrent Dilfer will start this week in place of Hasselbeck, whose separated left shoulder is too sore for him to play.    Coach Mike Holmgren said Wednesday that Hasselbeck aggravated the injury, which he's had since the third week of the season, against the New York Giants last Sunday.   \"There's a chance I might have him and he could play in an emergency-type situation, but he's pretty sore,\" Holmgren said.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Henry will sit out again this week with a sprained knee. Shawn Bryson will start for the second consecutive week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair missed practice Wednesday because of back pain.   \"I'm going to try to do some things tomorrow and hope it loosens up and not have as much pain as I had today,\" McNair said.   \"I'm not going to go out and try to force the issue. If it's still sore and still tight where I can't have all my mechanics right, I'm not going to force the issue.\"     The Titans listed him as questionable yet again Wednesday, but McNair likely will play \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1152\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e",
  "Jerome Bettis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PIT - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBettis sat out Wednesday's practice, and indicated he might not play in the regular season's final two games. \"You want to take care of the injury first and if that means not playing, that means not playing,\" Bettis told the \u003ci\u003ePittsburgh Post-Gazette\u003c/i\u003e. \"But you want to make sure you're healed up. The team playing as well as it has played allows me the opportunity to get healthy. I'm using it very, very wisely.\" \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=133297\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMartin Gramatica\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, K TB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "McCardell is listed as probable with a thigh injury. He should be able to start this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=235203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Chambers\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eChambers is listed as questionable with an ankle injury. He practiced on Wednesday and should be able to play this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1288\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJames McKnight\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcKnight is listed as questionable with an ankle injury. He practiced and is hopeful of playing this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",

  "Updated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHicks is expected to miss this week's game with a hamstring injury, and may miss the rest of the season. Eddie George should assume a regular workload once again. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1094\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEmmitt Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DAL - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith is day to day with a hip injury. He is expected to play this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=187401\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003ePeter Warrick\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CIN - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Warrick, who was benched late in last week's game, is expected to start. He has been a disappointment this year and Fantasy players should not use him at this point of the postseason.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1871\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTodd Bouman\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBouman (thumb) may attempt to practice late in the week. His status remains unclear for this week's game, and Spergon Wynn is available to start if needed. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026start=30\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e\u003cTABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=0 BGCOLOR=\"#000099\"\u003e\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=arial color=ffffff SIZE=\u003e\u003cB\u003eNFL Reports,\u0026nbsp;Transactions\u0026nbsp;\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e",
  "Wesley Walls\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE CAR - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWalls is listed as questionable with a knee injury. He was expected to be evaluated again on Thursday. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=1203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMuhsin Muhammad\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMuhammad (turf toe) is not expected to play this week, and may miss the rest of the season. Isaac Byrd will likely start in his place again. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=3837\u0026key=235216\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTravis Henry\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BUF - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/27/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",

  "McNair was excused from practice on Friday due to a family illness. However, he is far too risky to start at this point in the Fantasy season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4502\u0026key=1186\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBert Emanuel\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/29/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c16279416.1075855348665.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Save $.05 a gallon on the gas that keeps your car's engine clean. \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/226/sffer1228c.cgi\"\u003eClick here\u003c/a\u003e to apply online.\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Big E '01 12/31/01",
  "To": "martin.cuilla@enron.com",
  "Updated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFinneran is listed as probable with a knee injury. He is expected to play this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4502\u0026key=1499\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTyrone Davis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE GB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDavis has been elevated to the No. 2 tight end slot over rookie David Martin. He will see a considerable amount of playing time now that he is healthy, because Green Bay employs many double tight end sets in the red zone. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4502\u0026key=1612\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eOronde Gadsden\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Updated 12/30/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWalls (knee) has been declared inactive for Sunday's game. Kris Mangum will start in his place. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4502\u0026key=1871\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTodd Bouman\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/30/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBouman has been deactivated for Sunday's game. Spergon Wynn will start in his place. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4502\u0026key=187682\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDez White\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CHI - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/30/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWhite has been declared inactive for Sunday's game. David Terrell is expected to start in his place. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Wynn will start Sunday's game against the Green Bay Packers in place of the injured Todd Bouman. Wynn, who played in most of last week's loss to Jacksonville, is far too inexperienced to start this deep into the Fantasy season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football299.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4502\u0026key=1041\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDrew Bledsoe\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB NE - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/29/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAccording to published reports, the Chicago Bears are interested in acquiring Bledsoe. With Tom Brady seemingly entrenched as New England's quarterback, it seems that Bledsoe has become expendable to the Patriots. The move would certainly improve the Bears' passing game, but no deals would likely be made until sometime in the spring. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",

  "Brooks had a big game against San Francisco last weekend, throwing for 347 yards and two scores. He may be a bit inconsistent this season, but his potential to post huge numbers makes it tough to bench him, especially against a vulnerable Indianapolis defense.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1234\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eWillie Jackson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NO - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eJackson put up a huge game against San Francisco last weekend, posting 11 catches and 167 yards receiving. He'll face a questionable Indianapolis squad that is vulnerable to the pass in Week 10, so starting Jackson this week is a solid option. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1440\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eStephen Davis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB WAS - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated !",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Sat, 17 Nov 2001 05:28:58 -0800 (PST)",
  "EF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=235174\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Weinke\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB CAR - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAccording to published reports, Weinke will be the starting quarterback for Sunday's game against San Francisco. However, he's not worth starting on your Fantasy team. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=133263\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDaunte Culpepper\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eCulpepper is one pace for a good Fantasy season despite the lack of consistency in Minnesota's offense this season. He's one of the better quarterbacks in the league from a Fantasy perspective, and should be in your starting lineup on a weekly basis. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c27752509.1075861999372.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Michael Westbrook\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWestbrook has been inconsistent this season, but he has caught three touchdown passes in his last four games. He'll face a Denver secondary this weekend that is vulnerable at best, so starting him in deeper leagues is worth considering. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=235213\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Gardner\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGardner has been held in check in his last two games, catching only three passes for 38 yards. He does have a favorable matchup this weekend against Denver, however, so starting him is a good move. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=12411\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB!",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Save $.05 a gallon on the gas that keeps your car's engine clean. \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/226/sffer1113c.cgi\"\u003eClick here\u003c/a\u003e to apply online.\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Smith will return to the lineup Sunday against Philadelphia after missing two games with a sprained right knee. Cowboys Head Coach Dave Campo said after Friday's practice that Smith would \"be ready to play the majority of the game.\" His return bumps Troy Hambrick to fullback, but we wouldn't recommend you use either back against the stingy Eagles rush defense.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1184\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eFrank Sanders\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR ARI - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSanders (hamstring) was added to the NFL injury report on Friday and is now listed as questionable for Sunday's game against Detroit.  However, if you're completely desperate for a wideout in a larger league this week, Sanders' matchup against a vulnerable Detroit secondary is worth considering as long as he's able to play.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA !",

  "document.write('\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=o;ord='+random+'?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e');",
  "ge01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMuhsin Muhammad\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMuhammad finally had a somewhat productive game, catching six passes for 75 yards against St. Louis. He's had some success in the past against this week's opponent, San Francisco, so starting him is a decent move. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1028\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBrett Favre\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB GB - Frank \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFavre has been one of the best Fantasy quarterbacks in the league this season. He'll face an Atlanta team on Sunday with a very vulnerable secondary, so be sure to start Favre this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=187388\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBub!",
  "href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/5/3/sffer1113ffr.cgi\"\u003e",
  "http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1366\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eErnie Conwell\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE STL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eConwell has had a few down weeks, so starting him on your Fantasy team is somewhat of a gamble. With the lack of depth at tight end around the league, however, starting Conwell is something many Fantasy owners will have no choice but to do. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1456\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRichard Huntley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB CAR - Russell \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHuntley will be the likely starter this weekend against San Francisco, but don't be surprised if he splits carries with Nick Goings. Avoid starting either back in Week 10 if at all possible. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "reports please to to the URL below": "",
  "uben Droughns\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDroughns will likely split time with Lamont Warren in Detroit's backfield this weekend in James Stewart's absence. Neither back has much Fantasy value outside of deeper leagues, and starting them is a huge gamble. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1112\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eLamont Warren\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWarren will likely start in place of the injured James Stewart on Sunday against Arizona. He's split carries with Reuben Droughns, and is only worth starting as a last resort in larger Fantasy leagues. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026start=30\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e",
  "y.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair's status is still in question for Sunday's game against Cincinnati due to an injured right thumb. He threw the ball during individual drills Friday, and according to published reports, is likely to play despite not being 100 percent. We don't recommend McNair this week as a result.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=1094\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEmmitt Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DAL - Bass/Hull \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "z-Zahir Hakim\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR STL - Neal/McKay \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHakim has been inconsistent in recent weeks, so starting him on your Fantasy team is a gamble unless the matchup is right. He'll go up against a tough New England secondary in Week Ten, so avoid using him outside of deeper leagues. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2762\u0026key=133310\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTorry Holt\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR STL - Tori \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHolt continues to put up consistent yardage totals, but he's only scored only three touchdowns this season. He'll face a tough New England secondary this weekend, but he's still worth starting on your Fantasy team based on his potential to put up solid numbers. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e"
}

He'll face a Denver secondary this weekend that is vulnerable at best, so starting him in deeper leagues is wort!",
  "\u003cA HREF=http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/options-ereports?league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u003eclick here\u003c/A\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "\u003cBASE HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/\"\u003e",

  "Defensive end Michael McCrary will miss the rest of the season after undergoing knee surgery. His loss will certainly lower the sack output of the Baltimore defense and may mean the team will allow more passing yardage than usual. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=4658\u0026key=8\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e Cowboys\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, DT DAL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eLinebacker Dexter Coakley, who was expected to miss two weeks due to a sprained knee, will likely get the start on Thursday after being out for just one game. If he's in a situation where he can't perform at the level that we think can help our team, then we'll !",

  "\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cIMG HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2 WIDTH=14 HEIGHT=14 SRC=\"http": "//images.commissioner.com/images/eye_device_tiny.gif\"\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e\u003cFONT COLOR=\"#ffffff\"\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMake Selection\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e",
  "\u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/135/sffer1120tr.cgi\"\u003ehttp://www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/135/sffer1120tr.cgi\u003c/a\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2125\u0026key=235122\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMarvin Minnis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR KC - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMinnis is unlikely to be available for Sunday's game against Seattle due to the sprained ankle he suffered during a Nov. 11 game against the Jets. He will be replaced by Chris Thomas in the lineup at split end, and you should keep him reserved for this week.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2125\u0026key=1032\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMark Brunell\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB JAC - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2125\u0026key=1220\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DEN - Matty \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMike Shanahan said he does not know if Smith (ankle) will be sufficiently healed to play in Thursday's game against the Cowboys. \"We'll get a chance to evaluate that during the week and see,\" Shanahan told the \u003ci\u003eDenver Post\u003c/i\u003e. \"If he can help our football team, he'll play. If he's in a situation where he can't perform at the level that we think can help our team, then we'll keep him out and put somebody else in.\" \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2125\u0026key=245054\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBenjamin Gay\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB CLE - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe \u003ci\u003eCleveland Plain-Dealer\u003c/i\u003e",
  "Attention Fantasy Fans!  Subscribe to \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/224/sffer1120sn.cgi\"\u003eThe Sporting News\u003c/a\u003e now and get 4 FREE issues! Hurry!\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Brunell's nagging leg injury might sideline him for Sunday's game against Baltimore. He decided about two hours before last Sunday's kickoff that he couldn't play against Pittsburgh due to a strained right quadriceps. Jonathan Quinn has been preparing as if he will start the game, so right now you shouldn't count on Brunell this week as you set your lineups.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2125\u0026key=12753\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eFred Taylor\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB JAC - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTaylor received a second medical opinion Tuesday that indicated his severe groin injury could keep him out up to three months and possibly the remainder of the season, according to the \u003cI\u003eFlorida Times-Union\u003c/I\u003e. The diagnosis was that the injury still has not healed and will need more time to become healthy, and in the meantime Taylor has developed pain in!",

  "Owens suffered a sprained left knee and ankle during the overtime session of last weekend's game against Carolina. The injuries aren't considered serious, however, and Owens is expected to be in the starting lineup on Sunday Indianapolis. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2125\u0026start=31\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e\u003cTABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=0 BGCOLOR=\"#000099\"\u003e\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=arial color=ffffff SIZE=\u003e\u003cB\u003eTeams,\u0026nbsp;Rosters\u0026nbsp;\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003c/TABLE\u003e\u003c!-- Pizzahut Presenting Logo Spotlight tag - Do not remove until 12-31-01 --\u003e",
  "Patriots Head Coach Bill Belichick announced late Monday that Brady will remain the starting quarterback for the remainder of the season, barring injury. This relegates Drew Bledsoe to a backup role and makes him useless from a Fantasy perspective. Brady might have his hands full passing against the Saints on Sunday, but he is a fairly safe weekly starter otherwise.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2125\u0026key=15\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e Dolphins\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, DT MIA - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDefensive tackle Daryl Gardener could miss the remainder of the season due to a fragmented disc in his back. He will miss at least one month to rest and rehabilitate the injury before being re-evaluated. Gardener's absence hurts the Dolphins' rush defense, which might be burned a little more by opposing running backs in the upcoming weeks.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c!",

Brunell's status is still unclear for Sunday's game.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2125\u0026key=1151\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRicky Watters\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB SEA - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWatters' shoulder has not sufficiently healed enough for him to practice, says the \u003ci\u003eSeattle Times\u003c/i\u003e. He's posted three touchdowns and 217 yards receiving in his last two games, and should have another solid game vs. San Diego in Week 11. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2125\u0026key=187741\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTom Brady\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB NE - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "concussion last weekend vs. Denver, hasn't been feeling any after effects of the injury and should be under center for the 'Skins. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=2125\u0026key=12405\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJacquez Green\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR TB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGreen (abdomen) is expected to return to practice on Wednesday at full strength. {
  "Americas": "IBIT increased 31% to $701 million.  Natural gas volumes increased 6% to 26.7 Tbtu/d, and power volumes increased 77% to 290 million megawatt hours (MWh).",
  "Broadband Services": "IBIT losses were $(80) million in the current quarter compared to a $(20) million loss last year.  This quarter's results include significantly lower investment-related income and lower operating costs.",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=ANSI_X3.4-1968",
  "Corporate and other": "This segment includes the unallocated expenses associated with general corporate functions. This segment reported an IBIT loss of $(59) million compared to $(106) million a year ago.",
  "Date": "Tue, 16 Oct 2001 07:25:35 -0700 (PDT)",
  "Europe and Other Commodity Markets": "IBIT remained unchanged at $53 million as compared to last year.  While physical gas and power volumes increased, low volatility in these markets caused profitability to remain flat.",
  "Following are the highlights of our businesses": "",
  "From": "no.address@enron.com",
  "Global Assets": "This segment includes Elektro, Dabhol, TGS, Azurix and Enron Wind.  Third quarter IBIT remained unchanged at $19 million compared to last year.",
  "In addition, this quarter we announced one-time charges of $1.01 billion.  Over the past few quarters, we have conducted a thorough  review of our businesses and have decided to take certain charges to clear away issues that have clouded the performance and earnings potential  of our core businesses.  These charges include": "",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c29330214.1075853085654.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Natural Gas Pipelines": "IBIT increased slightly to $85 million in the third quarter.",
  "Portland General": "We reported an IBIT loss of $(17) million this quarter compared to IBIT of $74 million a year ago.  This loss is due to power contracts PGE entered into at prices that were significantly higher than actual settled prices during the third quarter.  Last week, we  announced an agreement to sell PGE to Northwest Natural.  This transaction is expected to close next year.",
  "Retail Services": "Enron Energy Services reported IBIT of $71 million, compared to $27 million a year ago.  So far this year, EES has completed more than 50 transactions with large customers and more than 95,000 deals with small business customers.",
  "Subject": "Third Quarter Earnings Results",
  "Transportation and Distribution": "",
  "Wholesale Services": "Total income before interest, minority interests and taxes (IBIT) increased 28% to $754 million in the third quarter.  Total wholesale physical volumes increased 65% to 88.2 trillion British thermal units equivalent per day (Tbtue/d).",
  "With our announcements this quarter we accomplished three things": "1) we showed continued strong earnings and earnings growth in our core businesses, 2) we cleared away those things that were clouding this superb performance in our core businesses, and 3) We expanded our reporting of financial results to increase transparency for our investors. To read the full earnings press release, go to www.enron.com/corp/pressroom/releases.",

  "Carter saw extensive action on Sunday as Stephen Davis played through back problems. He carried 18 times for 56 yards, and is a good backup to have if Davis in on your Fantasy team. He posted decent Fantasy numbers in Muhammad's absence, catching five passes for 69 yards in Carolina's 10-7 loss to Atlanta. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=734\u0026key=1203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMuhsin Muhammad\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Martin \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMuhammad missed Sunda!",
  "Chandler had a subpar game on Sunday, throwing for only 132 yards against Carolina. The Falcons chose to attack Carolina with their ground game, which was the reason for Chandler's poor Fantasy numbers. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=734\u0026key=1191\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDerrick Alexander\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR KC - JWillie \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/25/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAlexander caught two passes for 56 yards in his return from a rib injury.   "Fiedler threw for 262 yards, three TDs and no interceptions at Buffalo.   "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "In his return from a knee injury, Wheatley carried the ball five times for 17 yards.   "Sanders left Sunday's game against San Diego after re-aggravating a hamstring injury.   "Coal's advantage over gas": "It's cheap. Utilities paid an average of $1.20 per million Btu for coal last year, compared with $4.30 for gas (delivered).   ", RB MIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eChapman rushed for 90 yards on 22 carries against the Packers.   "\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football222.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=bige01\u0026owner=69677\u0026random=798\u0026key=1265\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eKeyshawn Johnson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR TB - Giggles \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 10/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eJohnson caught 10 passes for 159 yards against Pittsburgh.
